            <abstract>
                <p>Discusses GJR’s idea of subjecting plants to brief flashes of light.</p>
                <p>Hoped to see GJR in London, but was too tired.</p>
                <p>Delighted his book <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_5637.xml"><hi rend="italic">Movement in plants</hi></ref> has interested GJR.</p>
                <p>Asks if GJR has example of dogs calling on each other to go hunting; there is a case half a mile away.</p>
                <p>Has heard that Samuel Butler has abused him in his latest book, but he does not intend to look at it.</p>
            </abstract>
